Aim :
To understand and demonstrate different data types and operators used in Python programming.

Algorithm:
Start the program.
Create variables using different data types like integer, float, string, and boolean.
Display the values of these variables.
Perform arithmetic, comparison, and logical operations.
Print the results.
Stop the program.

Code:
a = 10
b = 5.5
c = "Hello"
d = True

print("Integer value:", a)
print("Float value:", b)
print("String value:", c)
print("Boolean value:", d)

print("\nArithmetic Operators")
print("Addition:", a + b)
print("Subtraction:", a - b)
print("Multiplication:", a * b)
print("Division:", a / b)

print("\nComparison Operators")
print("a > b:", a > b)
print("a < b:", a < b)
print("a == b:", a == b)

print("\nLogical Operators")
x = True
y = False
print("x and y:", x and y)
print("x or y:", x or y)
print("not x:", not x)


Output:
